<p>Provisionally deciphered and interpreted by Alexander Cunningham (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Cunningham1873_02"/></bibl>) based on the Mackenzie facsimile first published by James Prinsep (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Prinsep1837_01"/></bibl>). This interpretation corrected on several points through without integral new reading by Heinrich Lüders (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Luders1912_01"/></bibl>). Lüders' summary represented as a text edition in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Tsukamoto1996_01"/></bibl>. This digital edition by Arlo Griffiths &amp; Vincent Tournier combines what seem to be the most credible readings from previous scholars in the light of the published reproductions of the Mackenzie facsimile.</p>
